{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"@","kind":"attribute"},{"text":"MainActor","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"OUDSButton","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Hierarchies","anchor":"Hierarchies","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Four hierarchies are proposed for all layouts:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"default"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Default buttons are used for actions which are not mandatory or essential for the user."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"strong","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": The Strong “call for action” on the page should be singular and prominent, limited to one per view."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It should be reserved for the most critical action, such as “Next,” “Save,” “Submit,” etc.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"minimal","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Minimal buttons are commonly used for actions that are considered less crucial. They can be used independently or together with a strong button."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"negative","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Negative buttons should be used sparingly to warn of a destructive action,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"for example, delete or remove, typically resulting in the opening of a confirmation dialog."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"A button with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSButton.Hierarchy.Negative"},{"text":" hierarchy is not allowed as a direct or indirect child of an ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSColoredSurface"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":2,"text":"Code samples","type":"heading","anchor":"Code-samples"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["    \/\/ Icon only with default hierarchy","    OUDSButton(hierarchy: .default, icon: Image(\"ic_heart\")) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ Text only with negative hierarchy","    OUDSButton(hierarchy: .negative, text: \"Delete\") { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ Text and icon with strong hierarchy","    OUDSButton(hierarchy: .strong, icon: Image(\"ic_heart\"), text: \"Validate\") { \/* the action to process *\/ }"],"type":"codeListing"},{"level":2,"text":"Styles","anchor":"Styles","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Two style are available:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"default","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": used in the normal usage of button. The aspect of the button changes for following states disabled, pressed, hovered or normal (i.e. enabled)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"loading"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": used after button was clicked and probably data are requested before navigate to a next screen or get updated data."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"text":"Colored Surface","type":"heading","anchor":"Colored-Surface","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If button is placed on colored surface using "},{"code":"OUDSColoredSurface","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", the default colors (content, background and border) are automatically adjusted to switch to monochrom.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Remark: Today it is not allowed to place a Negative button on a colored surface.","t